subject: meta-quanta: gbs: Enable gbmc-sysinit for gbs and remove gbs-sysinit
commitMessage:
meta-quanta: gbs: Enable gbmc-sysinit for gbs and remove gbs-sysinit

Use the common gBMC sysinit init with some overrides instead of using
gbs specific scripts.

Tested:
```
$ systemctl status gbmc-sysinit
* gbmc-sysinit.service - gBMC System Initialization and release Host from reset
     Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/gbmc-sysinit.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)
    Drop-In: /lib/systemd/system/gbmc-sysinit.service.d
             `-service-override.conf
     Active: inactive (dead) since Thu 1970-01-01 00:01:24 UTC; 11s ago
    Process: 1438 ExecStart=/usr/bin/gbmc_sysinit.sh (code=exited, status=0/SUCCESS)
   Main PID: 1438 (code=exited, status=0/SUCCESS)

...
Jan 01 00:01:24 gbmc_sysinit.sh[1438]: Set gpio SPI_SW_SELECT #169 to direction low
Jan 01 00:01:24 systemd[1]: gbmc-sysinit.service: Deactivated successfully.
Jan 01 00:01:24 systemd[1]: Finished gBMC System Initialization and release Host from reset.
```

Host is booting up after.

Change-Id: I30dea3af8e3c4d55970728aba4c27f50dc19ea00
Signed-off-by: Willy Tu <wltu@google.com>
